name: Tim Adams Clare Valley Riesling 75Cl
description: Our 2006 Riesling is made from Riesling grapes grown on nine local vineyards, "Sheoaks", "Spring Farm", "Cherax Hill", "Smith's", "Larkey's Corner, "St Clare", "Maynard's", "Ireland's", and "Vines's".

The wine has fullness and strength without sweetness, with evident lime and floral aromas and flavours typical of this variety grown in the Clare Valley. The use of only free run juice (500 litres per tonne) is indicative of our commitment to quality.
The blend of these outstanding vineyards from a great vintage, has produced a wine which has immediate food compatibility, and with the potential for cellaring for at least ten years.
PromotionDescription: 155 extra points on Tesco Finest wine or port 75cl Excludes sparkling wine
